  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Then David put garrisons in Syria of Damascus,.... Which was Coele-Syria, and lay between Libanus and Antilibanus, the chief city of which was Damascus; which Curtius (q) calls Damascus of Syria, being the head of it, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Isaiah 7:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; in the principal places of which he put garrisons of soldiers to keep the country in subjection to him; or he put commanders or governors, as the Targum, in the, chief cities, and so Ben Gersom and R. Isaiah interpret it: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and the Syrians became servants to David, and brought gifts; or paid him tribute by way of homage, acknowledging themselves his subjects: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and the Lord preserved David whithersoever he went; he covered his head in the day of battle, and saved him from the hurtful sword. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(q) Hist. l. 3. c. 8. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
